            "id": "70c99cd85b914c2b93ac2",
            "questionText": "During a medical ultrasound imaging scan, high-frequency sound waves are used to visualize internal structures. A particular ultrasound pulse is emitted from a transducer and travels through the body, reflecting off a fetal structure. The reflected pulse is detected by the transducer after a total round-trip time of $!$40 \\mu s$!$. If the average speed of ultrasound in the tissue is $!$1540 \\text{ m/s}$!$, calculate the depth of the fetal structure from the transducer.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "7d16c628fe744f729576e",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying which formula relates the distance (one-way depth), the speed of sound, and the total round-trip time in echo-based measurements. Choose the correct formula from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "670671d3-985c-4a23-9178-05e06ebd3f7b"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = \\frac{vt}{2}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = vt$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = 2vt$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "d252628762304c0398173",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have the formula in mind, calculate the one-way travel time of the ultrasound pulse. (Hint: Divide the total round-trip time by 2.)",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.00002"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "s",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "ac6b0b488a164dd5b572f",
                    "stepText": "Now use the one-way travel time and the given speed of ultrasound to compute the depth of the fetal structure. Multiply the speed by the one-way travel time.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.0308"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "670671d3-985c-4a23-9178-05e06ebd3f7b"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
