        {
            "id": "2c66c78d1d2948d692922",
            "questionText": "On a hot summer day, a hiker shouts into a canyon. The air temperature is $!$30^\\circ\\text{C}$!$. Given that the speed of sound in air can be approximated by the formula $!$v = 331.3 + 0.606 \\times T_C\\text{ m/s}$!$, where $!$T_C$!$ is the temperature in degrees Celsius, and that the hiker's shout has a fundamental frequency of $!$150\\text{ Hz}$!$, calculate the wavelength of this sound wave.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "e999b5c85f2841dea3589",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula to calculate the speed of sound in air as a function of temperature. Please choose the correct expression from the options provided.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "2ba5ff20-2f55-4ade-8188-8b9b939a0062"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = 331.3 + 0.606 \\times T_C$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = 331.3 \\times T_C$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = T_C + 331.3$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = 0.606 \\times T_C$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "444b29ec54024c2bb2924",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, use the selected formula to calculate the speed of sound when the air temperature is $!$30^\\circ\\text{C}$!$. Compute this value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "349.48"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "2ba5ff20-2f55-4ade-8188-8b9b939a0062"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "daf990532a9b4321919ce",
                    "stepText": "Now that you have the speed of sound, let's identify the correct relationship between speed, frequency, and wavelength. Which formula correctly connects these three quantities?",
